## Early Age Of Riaz Ahmed Gohar Shahi
His Holiness Gohar Shahi exhibited extraordinary humility and kindness from a very young age. According to his village friends, he was deeply considerate of all living beings, no matter how small. For instance, when walking along the edge of a water canal, while others might inadvertently step on ants or insects, His Holiness would take great care to avoid harming them. This compassion extended to humans as well. If a car or bus broke down on a road near his village, he would not simply ignore the stranded passengers. Instead, he would personally prepare food and tea and take it to the spot to assist them. Even as a young boy, His Holiness showed a profound commitment to helping the poor and those in need, demonstrating a genuine desire to ease the struggles of others. His actions reflected a heart full of empathy and a spirit devoted to service.
From an early age, His Holiness Gohar Shahi displayed a profound interest in spirituality and Sufism. He would frequently visit the tombs of spiritual saints, seeking solace and divine connection in these sacred spaces as he pursued his quest for God. In his book, Roohani Safar , His Holiness recounts that as he reached the age of puberty, his yearning to become a saint reached its pinnacle. However, he found no clear path to fulfill this deep desire. Driven by an unwavering devotion, he would spend days and nights near the shrine of Baba Gohar Ali Shah , immersed in the recitation of religious verses, hoping to uncover the spiritual truths he sought so fervently. His dedication during these formative years laid the foundation for his profound spiritual journey.

## Spritual Journey of Riaz Ahmed Gohar Shahi
At the age of 20, His Holiness Riaz Ahmed Gohar Shahi embarked on his spiritual journey to find God. His first destination was Lal Bagh, a renowned Sufi site in Pakistan, where he began his search. However, his efforts were short-lived due to illusions and distractions caused by Satan. This initial failure weakened his belief in divinity and sainthood, leaving him disillusioned with religious scholars and Sufis. Disheartened, His Holiness shifted his focus to worldly life. He married, settled down, and had three children. For about 12 years, he lived a conventional life until he began experiencing profound spiritual dreams. In these dreams, a mysterious figure appeared, urging him to renounce worldly attachments and dedicate himself to religious practices. After about a year of these dreams, the figure gave a final command: to leave worldly life within three days to purify his lower self. In 1975, following this divine instruction, His Holiness journeyed to Sehwan Sharif, the shrine of Sufi Saint Lal Shahbaz Qalandar. His Holiness recounted his first night at Sehwan Sharif. While engaging in zikr (chanting the name of God), he fell asleep and saw a gathering of saints in his dream. Among them was a tall, robust man with a striking appearance, including a large build and long mustaches. The saint pointed towards him and recited a Punjabi verse: "Asaan haan Qalandar dewaany lajpaal dy" ("We are the ecstatic followers of Qalandar, the protector of the helpless.") From that night onward, His Holiness's heartbeat began to rhythmically chant the name of God. Overwhelmed with joy, he realized that the God he had been searching for in jungles, caves, and distant places had been within his own heart all along.
## Incident in Jungle With Riaz Ahmed Gohar Shahi
His Holiness shared a remarkable incident from the Laal Bagh jungle. He recounted that one day, a tall, elderly man appeared and silently stared at him before walking towards a nearby canal. Around 3 AM, the same man returned. In the darkness, his eyes glowed like fire, casting an eerie presence. As he approached closer, His Holiness felt an intense shock course through his body. At that very moment, His Holiness's heartbeat began chanting the name of God at a rapid pace. Suddenly, a radiant white ball of light emerged from his chest and shot towards the old man. The glowing orb struck the man, causing him to step back in pain. Angered, the man began hurling stones at His Holiness. In this extraordinary moment, His Holiness saw a figure, identical to himself, emerge from his own body. This spiritual form stood before the tall man while His Holiness's physical body became invisible to him. It seemed to be his spiritual body—a divine manifestation. The spiritual body began reciting something and blew its breath towards the tall man, inflicting pain on him. In retaliation, the tall man recited his own verses and blew them back, causing discomfort to the spiritual body. This spiritual confrontation lasted for about 30 minutes. Eventually, flames started emerging from the tall man's mouth. In response, the spiritual body flew like a bird and perched atop a nearby palm tree. Enraged, the tall man threw stones, but his fiery breath and projectiles failed to reach the spiritual body. The tall man, consumed with anger, began climbing the palm tree to reach the spiritual body. However, just as he approached, the spiritual body soared into the sky like an eagle, leaving the tall man staring in disbelief and defeat. Realizing his inability to confront this divine entity, the tall man left the jungle, bewildered and anxious. AFollowing this incident, His Holiness's spiritual body began appearing to various people in different places. People reported seeing him in Sehwan, and when they came to the Laal Bagh jungle, they would also find him there simultaneously. This marked the emergence of nine other human-like figures resembling His Holiness. These spiritual forms joined him during zikr (chanting the name of God), during prayers, and even stood as protectors when he slept. They were not just passive beings; they actively helped those in need, assisting followers in their dreams or even physically appearing to guide and support them. This miraculous event further demonstrated the divine nature and spiritual power of His Holiness, strengthening the faith of those around him.

## Leaving Jungle
After spending approximately three years in the jungle, His Holiness received a divine command from God to leave the jungle and return to Hyderabad. The instruction was clear: serve humanity by sharing the knowledge of God and helping people reconnect with the Divine. Upon returning to Hyderabad, His Holiness chose a serene spot near Jamshoro, behind the Textbook Board. There, he built a simple hut that became a sanctuary for those seeking solace and spiritual guidance. His Holiness dedicated himself to healing the emotionally distressed and purifying people's hearts through the practice of zikr (chanting the name of God). People who had previously encountered His Holiness during his time in Sehwan began visiting this new location to continue seeking his blessings and wisdom. Word of his presence spread quickly, and his humble hut started attracting students from universities and medical colleges. These young minds showed a profound interest in the spiritual teachings and practices of zikr that His Holiness imparted. However, this growing attention did not sit well with everyone. The principal of one of the universities, noticing the students' increasing visits, tried to stop them but failed to deter their determination. Frustrated, the principal eventually instructed his staff to dismantle the hut. Following these orders, the hut was torn down. Despite this setback, His Holiness remained unwavering in his mission. He relocated to a new place within Hyderabad and continued his sacred work. Undeterred by obstacles, he persisted in awakening people's hearts, guiding them towards a deeper connection with God, and spreading the message of love and divinity. His efforts inspired countless individuals, leaving an indelible mark on their spiritual journeys.
## Anjuman Sarfuroshan-e-Islam - First Organization of Riaz Ahmed Gohar Shahi
His Holiness Riaz Ahmed Gohar Shahi, in his book Roohani Safar, shares an insightful account of how the journey of spreading the Divine message began and need for an organization was felt. His Hollines writes:
- "In the beginning, when people started visiting me and showing interest, I thought, why not engage their services to spread this Divine message? At first, I approached elderly people to talk about heart zikr (chanting the name of God from the heart). They listened attentively and enjoyed the discourse, but none were willing to practice it. Then, I decided to reach out to the Islamic scholars. While a few nodded in agreement, the majority opposed this spiritual knowledge and the concept of heart awakening. Disheartened by their rejection, I turned my focus to the younger generation. Young hearts are relatively untainted compared to the older ones, and they not only accepted the message but also engaged with it practically. As a result, this Divine message of love and heart awakening began to spread rapidly—through mosques, streets, and bazaars. The number of lovers and practitioners of this message increased abruptly."
To manage the growing number of followers and the widespread interest in this spiritual mission, His Holiness founded the Anjuman Sarfroshan-e-Islam Organization. Under his supervision, this organization played a pivotal role in awakening and purifying the hearts of ordinary people, elevating their spiritual awareness, and spreading the Divine message of love and enlightenment. The organization's efforts transformed countless lives, fostering a profound connection with God and helping individuals find peace and purpose through spiritual practices. Through this structured approach, the mission of heart awakening continued to grow and inspire people from all walks of life.
## Mission of His Holiness Riaz Ahmed Gohar Shahi
His Holiness Riaz Ahmed's mission is a divine calling to awaken and purify the hearts of humanity, fostering a deep connection with God that transcends all barriers of religion, ethnicity, region, or color . His vision is universal, rooted in love and spirituality, and aims to unite people under the umbrella of Divine Love. Through the practice of heart purification and heart-invocation, His Divine Eminence initiated thousands of seekers onto the mystical path, inspiring them to embark on a journey toward divine enlightenment. His teachings resonated across diverse faiths, as he was warmly welcomed by people of all religions to share his spiritual wisdom. Whether in Mosques, Hindu Temples, Churches, or Sikh Temples, His Divine Eminence delivered profound spiritual lectures that touched the hearts of all who listened. Through his grace, countless individuals from various walks of life experienced the transformative power of heart-invocation, leading them closer to God. His Divine Eminence's teachings sparked repentance and spiritual awakening in countless men and women, guiding them toward a life centered on divine love and compassion. Many were inspired to abandon paths of despair and turn toward God, finding solace and purpose in his words. Furthermore, his spiritual grace extended to the realm of healing, restoring health to numerous individuals suffering from ailments deemed incurable. His presence brought hope, light, and healing, making a lasting impact on the lives of countless individuals. In essence, His Divine Eminence Riaz Ahmed stands as a beacon of divine love and guidance, breaking down worldly divisions to connect humanity with the Creator, offering a universal message of love, hope, and spiritual awakening. According to Gohar Shahi when Name of GOD enters human heart, it creates divine love within that heart, that divine light  compels its holder to love GOD and His creation.
## Disappearnce of His Holiness Riaz Ahmed Gohar Shahi
His Holiness Riaz Ahmed revealed in His presence that He would disappear for some time and later reappear in this world alongside Jesus Christ. This return is destined to counter the satanic powers and reconnect humanity with God through the teachings of love and heart awakening.
In anticipation of His disappearance, His Holiness appointed Younus AlGohar as His Divine Eminence's Representative. He declared, "Whoever wishes to meet Gohar Shahi (Himself) should meet Younus AlGohar." This appointment was a clear directive to ensure the continuation of His divine mission.
Despite the explicit instructions and foreknowledge provided by His Holiness about His disappearance, certain individuals, including His sons and some family members, falsely declared Him dead. They constructed a tomb in His name and began collecting money from followers, exploiting His Holiness's legacy for personal gain.
Furthermore, they rejected the divine order of His Holiness Riaz Ahmed Gohar Shahi to follow Younus AlGohar as His Representative. Instead, they unlawfully proclaimed themselves the inheritors of His mission and continue to mislead some followers with deceptive practices.
Today, His Holiness's sacred mission is under the guidance and supervision of Younus AlGohar through the establishment of a new organization, Messiah Foundation International. This organization is dedicated to preserving and spreading the true teachings and mission of His Holiness Riaz Ahmed.
# Younus AlGohar
**Younus AlGohar** (born: 16 June 1969) is a Representative of Gohar Shahi and co-founder of the Messiah Foundation International, also known as the Kalki Avatar Foundation and Mehdi Foundation International. This organization is dedicated to spreading the mystical teachings of His Holiness Riaz Ahmed Gohar Shahi and upholds the belief that Shahi is the prophesied Messiah (Mahdi).
In 1983, at the age of 15, Younus AlGohar encountered His Divine Eminence Riaz Ahmed Gohar Shahi for the first time. This meeting marked the beginning of an extraordinary spiritual journey. Over the next 18 years, he remained a devoted and close disciple of His Holiness, learning directly from him and embracing his divine mission. Younus AlGohar continued to serve as a disciple until His Holiness’s disappearance in 2001.
Younus AlGohar also manages the Alra TV channel, which is accessible on almost all major social media platforms. He goes live every night at 10:30 PM UK time, engaging with audiences worldwide. During these live sessions, people ask questions about spirituality, the secrets of divine love, and the mysteries of the universe. Younus AlGohar provides detailed and enlightening answers, drawing from the teachings of His Holiness Riaz Ahmed Gohar Shahi.
This innovative use of social media to disseminate the message of Gohar Shahi has significantly contributed to the mission’s growth. It has made the teachings more accessible and relatable to a global audience, leading to increased awareness and widespread recognition of the divine mission.
## Messiah Foundation International
**RAGS International** was founded by His Holiness Riaz Ahmed Gohar Shahi in 1980. In 2000, it was renamed Messiah Foundation International (MFI) to reflect the evolving scope of its divine mission. The first center for MFI was established in London, which continues to serve as the organization’s headquarters.
Since its inception, MFI has expanded globally, establishing centers in numerous countries, including Canada, the USA, South Korea, Sri Lanka, Japan, Australia, India, Greece, Thailand, Bangladesh, Taiwan, Pakistan, and Nepal. These centers are devoted to spreading the spiritual teachings of His Holiness and fostering divine love and heart awakening across the world.
At this time, the only valid organization is Messiah Foundation International. All other organizations are not recognized as valid.
